# Leo-Profanity Project

Profanity filter library based on Shutterstock dictionary. Supports multiple languages (English, French, Russian).

## Project Structure

- `src/index.js` - Main source code with LeoProfanity object
- `test/index.spec.js` - Test file using Mocha/Chai
- `dictionary/default.json` - Default English profanity word list
- `example/` - Usage examples (CommonJS, ES6, browser)
- `doc/` - Generated JSDoc documentation

## Key Information

- Package name: `leo-profanity`
- Main branch: `master`
- License: MIT
- Repository: https://github.com/jojoee/leo-profanity

## Supported Languages

- English (en) - built-in via `dictionary/default.json`
- French (fr) - optional dependency `french-badwords-list`
- Russian (ru) - optional dependency `russian-bad-words`

## Core API Methods

Public methods on LeoProfanity object:
- `list()` - Get current word list
- `check(str)` - Check if string contains profanity
- `clean(str, replaceKey, nbLetters)` - Replace profanity words
- `badWordsUsed(str)` - Get list of bad words found
- `add(data)` - Add words to list
- `remove(data)` - Remove words from list
- `reset()` - Reset to default English dictionary
- `clearList()` - Clear all words
- `getDictionary(name)` - Get dictionary by name
- `loadDictionary(name)` - Load dictionary
- `addDictionary(name, words)` - Create new dictionary
- `removeDictionary(name)` - Remove dictionary
